  "body": "With the release of [v0.9.2](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/releases/tag/v0.9.2). This issue tracks to the progress to align Prysm to v.0.9.2\r\n\r\nThe v0.9.2 consists of the following:\r\n\r\n### Aggregation Refactor\r\n\r\nWe need to refactor entirely how aggregation works based on https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1484\r\n\r\n### Beacon chain\r\n\r\n- [x] remove Hash alias and add Root alias for Bytes32(https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1478)\r\n- [x] reduce minimum genesis validator count in mainnet config (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1467)\r\n- [x] Use public validator API methods defined in https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/ethereumapis\r\n- [x] Use custom state SSZ (not required for restart, can be rolled out)\r\n\r\n### Fork choice\r\n\r\n- [x] harden fork choice to a few scenarios (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1477)\r\n\r\n### Validator\r\n\r\n- [x] provide explicit directives to validators on which attestation topics to join and when(https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1476)",
